args: Could it be behind this door?\n...Aye, it COULD!
Activating stonetech engine!\nReactor mana charge risin'...\n50 percent... 80 percent...100 percent!
Blast me! I can't even make a dent!

Hard to fathom a rokkan like me
still don't have enough power.
Guess they don't be callin' it the
＂continent's hardest ore＂ as a jape.
Still, I need this ore to produce a fine\nweapon. Without it, I'll just be losin' to\nRamona and the lasses again.
I need more power. Which means...
Ho there, cousin! I'm lookin' to fashion\na bit of a specialty machine.
What kind of machine are\nwe talking about here?
I need a machine what can attach to\nme own arm and make me stronger.\nI need a Smithy Arm!
With a Smithy Arm, I can be breakin' up\nthe hardest ore to fashion fine weapons\nwhat'll win me the Golden Anvil.

You mean the tournament they use
to find the best smithy in the world? 
Mmm, this is gonna be a tight order;
that contest is coming up real soon.

But if it's a Smithy Arm you want,
then I'll whip one up right away.
I just got a new stonetech engine
that'll be perfect for the job!
Nay, no need. Just give me the parts\nand I'll fashion it on me own.
No offense meant, cousin, but a true\nsmith has to mine their own ore.

No offense taken. But while I appreciate
your grit, you might want to reconsider.
Fashioning machines and smithing
weapons aren't the sa—
You there! Engineer!\nYou're coming with us!
Looks like this dog needs to learn\nwho holds his leash. Hah!
Huh? Is this kid another engineer?
You got me. Still, might as well\nbring her along.
Am I...in a cart? ...Nnngh!\nI can't move me hands'n feet!
You've been tied up. Stop struggling\nbefore you do even more damage.
These people are wearing the crest of\nthe Dyrenell Empire, but I can't figure\nout what they want for the life of me.
Enough! This will all be for nothing\nif you beat him to a bloody pulp.
What's going on here?\nWhat do you want from us?
You're here to work, dog! You will build\na new mechanical weapon in the service\nof the glorious empire!
You're scoopin' up engineers and\nsmiths what to craft a WEAPON?
If you're making some kind of machine,\nyou only need engineers.
Lazry is a blacksmith, not an engineer.\nYou should let her go.
Does that mean you'll let her go?
Ha! Not likely. Blacksmiths are being\nused to make weapons in a different\narea, so we'll be sending her there.
Then it looks like I have no choice...\nHAAAAAH!
Can't believe those men are gonna force\nthat poor engineer to build a weapon.
I bet gold to granite they're takin' him\nto the abandoned mine down the road.
I gotta be helpin' him, so I do.
He saved me life, and that's a debt\nI can't let go unpaid.
This sounds like a job for me Smithy Arm!
With that, I can tunnel into the mine and\ngive the soldiers a proper thrashin'!
I feel right low usin' the engineer's\nworkshop without tellin' the man,\nbut I'm sure he'll understand.
Right then! Time to get to it!
Hmm... So this bit goes here,\nand this one goes...here?
Aye, there she is! Look at the power flow\nfrom that stonetech engine!
Except I'm not sure how to turn it off?\nAch! The engine is runnin' outta control!\nLemme just tinker with that...
Right then! She's ready for testin'!
Ow! Ow ow owwwww! Blast it all!\nJoints aren't supposed to be bendin'\nthat way! Oooooow!
That engineer was right: Makin' machines\nis MUCH different from smithin'.
But I won't be givin' up—I'm gonna\ncrack this nut and save him!
